Here’s what changed.

**Change:** Re-export the tree primitives from the `@procertus-ui/ui` root barrel in `packages/ui/src/index.ts`:

```12:15:packages/ui/src/index.ts
/** Sewdn components copied from the local shadcn-based UI library. */
export * from "./components/sewdn";
/** ReUI: headless-tree based tree primitives. */
export { Tree, TreeItem, TreeItemLabel, TreeDragLine } from "./components/reui/tree";
```

**Why:** `Tree`, `TreeItem`, and `TreeItemLabel` are defined and exported in `components/reui/tree.tsx`, but the main entry only re-exported `components/ui`, stepper, timeline, sewdn, etc. Anything importing them from `@procertus-ui/ui` had no matching export, which caused the TypeScript error.

**Verification:** `read_lints` reports no issues for `ProductTreePanel.tsx` or `index.ts`. `oxlint` passes on `src/index.ts`. Full `tsc` for `@procertus-ui/ui` / `@procertus-ui/ui-certification` still fails on unrelated existing problems (path aliases, sewdn, stories), not on these imports.

[REDACTED]

